            {
              "renderType": "rich-text",
              "tag": "p",
              "content": [
                {
                  "content": "I was initially tasked with leading design on this project but due to changes on the team also took on more front-end development tasks. One of the main tasks was creating the slider of featured news articles at the top of the newsroom landing page. While sliders typically have many "
                },
                {
                  "tag": "a",
                  "link": "https://www.a11yproject.com/posts/a-guide-to-troublesome-ui-components/#carousels",
                  "content": "technical accessibility issues"
                },
                {
                  "content": " associated with them we looked at examples like product sliders on apple.com and "
                },
                {
                  "tag": "a",
                  "link": "https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/carousel/examples/carousel-2-tablist/",
                  "content": "carousel patterns"
                },
                {
                  "content": " from the W3C ARIA guides that use tab roles and structures to control and communicate slider state. We mapped this out with annotations (adapted from "
                },
                {
                  "tag": "a",
                  "link": "https://www.figma.com/community/file/953682768192596304",
                  "content": "Indeed's A11y Annotation Kit"
                },
                {
                  "content": " on top of the visual design to consider and break down the interaction into focus states, reading and tabbing order, roles and labels before jumping into development. This was a helpful reference throughout implementation."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "renderType": "container",
          "paddingTop": "l",
          "paddingTopLarge": "2xl",
          "paddingBottom": "l",
